post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_32800866_32800889_0": {"length": 13, "quality": 0.8666666666666667, "section_id": 6146}, "so_32800866_32800889_1": {"length": 14, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 26}}, "n3337": {"so_32800866_32800889_0": {"length": 13, "quality": 0.8666666666666667, "section_id": 5909}, "so_32800866_32800889_1": {"length": 14, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 23}}, "n4659": {"so_32800866_32800889_0": {"length": 13, "quality": 0.8666666666666667, "section_id": 7642}, "so_32800866_32800889_1": {"length": 14, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 26}}}, "32800889": {"Id": "32800889", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>From [expr.shift]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_32800866_32800889_0\">The operands shall be of integral or unscoped enumeration type and integral promotions are performed. The type of the result is that of the promoted left operand.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>From [conv.prom]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_32800866_32800889_1\">A prvalue of type <code>bool</code> can be converted to a prvalue of type <code>int</code>, with <code>false</code> becoming zero and <code>true</code> becoming one.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Integral promotion on <code>bool</code> produces <code>int</code>. So the result type of <code>true &lt;&lt; (any integral type)</code> is <code>int</code>. <code>true &lt;&lt; static_cast&lt;char&gt;(9)</code> after integral promotion is the same as <code>1 &lt;&lt; 9</code>, which is well-defined as <code>512</code>. </p>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "2069064", "LastActivityDate": "2015-09-26T19:04:08.443", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2015-09-26T19:01:08.397", "ParentId": "32800866", "CommentCount": "4", "OwnerUserId": "2069064", "LastEditDate": "2015-09-26T19:04:08.443"}, "32800866": {"ViewCount": "95", "Body": "<p>Consider the following code:</p>\n<pre><code>// E1 &lt;&lt; E2 with E1 bool, and E2 an integer\ntrue &lt;&lt; static_cast&lt;char&gt;(1);\ntrue &lt;&lt; static_cast&lt;short int&gt;(1);\ntrue &lt;&lt; static_cast&lt;int&gt;(1);\ntrue &lt;&lt; static_cast&lt;unsigned int&gt;(1);\ntrue &lt;&lt; static_cast&lt;long long int&gt;(1); \ntrue &lt;&lt; static_cast&lt;long long unsigned int&gt;(1);\n</code></pre>\n<p>When doing the operation, is <code>E1</code> promoted as the same type as <code>E2</code>, or is it promoted first to <code>int</code> and then to <code>std::common_type&lt;E1, E2&gt;::type</code>?</p>\n<p>In other words, is:</p>\n<pre><code>true &lt;&lt; static_cast&lt;char&gt;(9);\n</code></pre>\n<p>defined, or undefined behaviour ?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "32800889", "Title": "In the expression bool << integer, is bool promoted to int, or to the same type as the integer?", "CreationDate": "2015-09-26T18:58:56.420", "Id": "32800866", "CommentCount": "1", "LastEditDate": "2015-10-11T17:33:09.420", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "3640770", "LastActivityDate": "2015-10-11T17:33:09.420", "Score": "3", "OwnerUserId": "882932", "Tags": "<c++><implicit-conversion><integer-promotion>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});